commit.message:
Fix network performance issue on arm64 for runv

Network performance in runv is lower significantly
than in virtual machine started by qemu,as vnet_hdr
feature is not enabled in runv when get access to
a tun/tap device. Adding CIFF_VNET_HDR flag to GetTapFd
func will fixed that issue.

Signed-off-by: Jianyong Wu <Jianyong.Wu@arm.com>
Signed-off-by: Wei Chen <Wei.Chen@arm.com>

commit.message:
update vendor

Signed-off-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>

shim: run shim in specified netns if necessary

In docker case, we let the shim to own a netns and for shared netns
containers, we let new shims join existing netns.

We used to use nsenter to do it for runv shim, but kata shim does not
support nsenter. So we change to handle it when spawning new shims and
it works for both runv shim and kata shim.

Signed-off-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>

commit.message:
api: hypervisor: create agent container when adding

Kata shim does not wait for any signals so we need to make sure
the agent container is created in `runv create` otherwise shim
will fail to find the container in the agent.

This changes runv API such that AddContainer() needs to be called
_after_ other container resources (like rootfs/volume/NIC) are
added.

Signed-off-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>

cli: do not signal kata shim

kata-shim does not handle SIGUSR1 on its own.

Signed-off-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>

agent: fix kata agent SignalProcess ExecId

Kata Agent uses empty ExecId to signal all processes of a container.

Signed-off-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>

shim: invoke kata shim if asked

Signed-off-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>

shim: move out runv shim cmdlines

In preparation for kata shim.

Signed-off-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>

cli: skip adding nic if it is not configured

The kata container is still missing network config capability.

Signed-off-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>

cli: add namespace requirements to default spec

So that the Kata agent can run a bundle with the default spec.

Signed-off-by: Peng Tao <bergwolf@gmail.com>

commit.message:
qemu: clear persist flag on tap device

In the scenario which tap device was not created by qemu but passed
in(e.g, with some cni plugin), there was IFF_PERSIST flag set on it,
the flag need to be cleared to make sure tap device removed cleanly
on qemu exit.
